It's located on the top floor (second floor) of a walk-up building. All the rooms of the apartment are really big for New York standards and the apartment is quiet.

The bedroom has a comfortable bed, a large desk, a nightstand, a tall mirror and shelves for your clothes. You can also hang some clothes and store your shoes in one of the large closets in the hallway. I provide clean sheets and towels.

There is a good heating system throughout the apartment and I also have extra blankets and a portable heater to be ready for the cold winter months ahead. The internet is very fast but please note that I don't have a tv. There is a laundromat open 24/7 right across the street.

I absolutely love my street and neighborhood -- full of bars, cool coffee shops, and cute boutiques. The apartment is ideally located next to the L, G, J, M, Z subway lines (about a 5-10 minute walk to any) and a 10-15 minute walk from the waterfront with great views of Manhattan. If you're not familiar with the area, I'll be more than happy to share my favorite spots with you!

I'm looking for an extremely clean, quiet and respectful subletter, and someone who can be discreet about the sublet thing. Please no parties of any kind, overnight guests, and absolutely no smoking. I also have several plants that I would hate to see die so it would be great if my subletter could water them once in a while.

Many thanks for checking my listing out and please feel free to reach out with questions. You can come by and view my place any time this week!
